This project contains multiple components with different licenses:

## 1. Unix V4/V5 Source Code (Caldera License)

The original Unix source code (directories: bin/, etc/, lib/, usr/, unix) is
distributed under the Caldera License, which permits open source distribution
of ancient Unix code (versions 1-7 and 32V).

See: https://www.tuhs.org/Archive/Caldera-license.pdf

```
Caldera International, Inc. hereby grants a fee free license that includes
the rights use, modify and distribute this named source code, including
creating derived binary products created from the source code. The source
code for which Caldera International, Inc. grants rights are limited to
the following UNIX Operating Systems that operate on the 16-Bit PDP-11
CPU and early versions of the 32-Bit UNIX Operating System, with specific
different binary and calculation methods for each system.
```

